reviewText: 2 greatgrandaughters.. enough said.. hope they like it.. maybe when they are a little older.. too many ads and coming attractions. it would be nice to have the ads at the end of disk not the beginning..
Title: Sing-Along Songs: Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious - I Love to Laugh

reviewText: This is a delightful DVD.  My grandkids love it and watch it all the time.  They have never seen Mary Poppins but they sure love these songs, plus the other songs on it.  Always makes them laugh too and they dance and just have a great time.  They are 4 and 6 years of age.  A boy and girl.
summary: Sing-Along Song: I Love to Laugh
Title: Sing-Along Songs: Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious - I Love to Laugh

reviewText: If you love Disney as much as we do, then you will love all of these sing-a-longs! This is all my son will currently let us watch in the car (this one and about 4 other sing-a-longs we got for a Disney trip last year). Good buy!
Title: Sing-Along Songs: Supercalifragilisticexpialidocious - I Love to Laugh

reviewText: Our two year old LOVES the Lion King Sing a long, but really doesn't care for this one.  It just doesn't interest him.  I gave it three stars because I thought it was OK, I always liked Mary Poppins, but I think the lack of animation in several of the songs is probably not as exciting for the kiddos.

reviewText: All of the Disney Sing A long Song DVD's are great for little kids.  My children loved them as they were growing up.  Now my granddaughter is enjoying all of the Sing a long songs.  She is almost 2 years old and dances in front of the movies.

reviewText: I have looked at all the Disney singalongs available and read all the reviews, and not ONE of them lists the songs performed, anywhere. Who would buy a music DVD with no idea what songs are on it? I wouldn't, and won't.Amazon, bad job.
